<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ861209-0091 </DOCNO><HL> McDonnell DouglasObtains Navy JobsOf $277.4 Million</HL><DD> 12/09/86</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> MD BLL UTX GM GMHAEROSPACE (ARO)DEFENSE DEPARTMENT (DEF) </IN><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Units of McDonnell Douglas Corp. won Navy contracts totaling $277.4 million for production of FA-18 aircraft and development of the T-45TS jet-aircraft training system.    Ball Aerospace Systems, a unit of Ball Corp., received a $37.5 million Air Force contract for a Strategic Defense Initiative experiment.    Sikorsky Aircraft, a unit of United Technologies Corp., was awarded a $32.9 million Navy contract to produce CH-53E and MH-53E helicopters.    Western Petroleum Co. received a $14.7 million Defense Logistics Agency contract for jet fuel.    Hughes Aircraft Co., a unit of General Motors Corp., won a $12 million Navy contract for production and test equipment for Phoenix missiles. </TEXT></DOC>